165. Penalty for certain offences.
(1) If any person—
(a) fails to furnish a return of total income within the time allowed under sub-section (1) of section 139 or fails to disclose fully and truly all material facts necessary for computation of his total income;

(b) fails to keep, maintain or retain books of account and other documents in the manner laid down in section 122;

(c) fails to comply with any notice, order or direction issued under sub-section (3) of section 170;

(d) fails to comply with any notice, order or direction issued under sub-section (1) of section 171;

(e) fails to appear before the Income-tax Authority when required to do so under sub-section (1) of section 172;

(f) fails to submit to any test of sample or to comply with any other process under sub-section (2) of section 173;

(g) contravenes any of the provisions of clause (ii) of sub-section (4) of section 175;

(h) fails to comply with any notice, order or direction issued under sub-section (1) of section 176;

(i) fails to give information required by an Income-tax Authority under sub-section (2A) of section 131;

(j) fails to produce accounts and documents when required to do so by an income-tax authority in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (2B) of section 131, or produces or furnishes false evidence;

(k) claims any relief or deduction or allowance in respect of which he is not entitled;

(l) fails to comply with any order passed by an Income-tax Authority under clause (a) or clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 254, or with the direction given under sub-section (3) of section 250;

(m) being a person responsible for deducting tax at source under Chapter XVII fails to pay in accordance with the provisions of that Chapter such tax to the credit of the Government within the prescribed time;

(n) being an employer, fails to pay or disburse employee’s contribution to the provident fund or family pension fund as required by sub-section (1) of section 8 of the Employees' Provident Funds and Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1952 (19 of 1952);

(o) fails to comply with any order passed by an Income-tax Authority under sub-section (3) of section 115WB or section 115WD;

(p) being a seller, fails to get his accounts audited in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1) of section 44AB and fails to furnish a report of such audit as required under sub-section (2A) of that section or gets his accounts audited by a person who is not eligible for appointment as an auditor under section 141;

(q) being a buyer, fails to get the accounts referred to in sub-section (3) of section 44AB audited and fails to furnish a report of such audit as required under sub-section (4) of that section or gets his accounts audited by a person who is not eligible for appointment as an auditor under section 141;

(r) being a seller, fails to pay the tax collected at source in accordance with the provisions of Chapter XVII-B before the prescribed date;

(s) being a buyer, fails to pay the tax payable by him under sub-section (1) of section 206C or sub-section (1A) thereof, as the case may be, before the prescribed date;

(t) collects any amount as tax in accordance with the provisions of Chapter XVII-BB and fails to pay such amount to the credit of the Central Government before the prescribed date;

(u) fails to comply with the provisions of sub-section (1A) of section 206C;

(v) being a person responsible for deducting tax at source under Chapter XVII-BB, fails to pay in accordance with the provisions of that Chapter such tax to the credit of the Government within the prescribed time; or

(w) having been served with a notice under sub-section (1) of section 153A fails to comply with any of the requirements of that section,
he shall be liable to pay by way of penalty a sum equal to the amount of tax sought to be evaded by reason of the default or failure in respect of which the penalty is imposed:

Provided that where the person concerned proves that there was no possibility of evasion of tax in the circumstances of the case, no penalty shall be imposable.

Explanation.—For the purposes of this sub-section and sub-sections (2) and (3), "tax sought to be evaded" means the tax as determined under section 158BCA or section 158BCC or section 158BE, as the case may be.

(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), if any person who has made a return under section 139 in respect of income chargeable to tax fails to comply with any notice, order or direction issued under sub-section (4) of that section, he shall be liable to pay by way of penalty a sum equal to one hundred per cent of the amount of tax sought to be evaded by reason of the default or failure in respect of which the penalty is imposed.

(3) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), if any person who has made a return under section 139 in respect of income chargeable to tax—

(a) fails to comply with any notice, order or direction issued under sub-section (5) of that section; or

(b) fails to disclose fully and truly all material facts necessary for computation of his total income, he shall be liable to pay by way of penalty a sum equal to three times the amount of tax sought to be evaded by reason of the default or failure in respect of which the penalty is imposed.

(4) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), if any person who has made a return under section 139 in respect of income chargeable to tax, fails to comply with any notice, order or direction issued under sub-section (1) of section 142 and the Assessing Officer is satisfied that such failure was due to willful concealment of particulars of his income or willful furnishing of inaccurate particulars of such income, he shall be liable to pay by way of penalty a sum equal to three times the amount of tax sought to be evaded by reason of the default or failure in respect of which the penalty is imposed.

